`IFormFile` buffers the entire request body into memory by default. For large files, read the raw request body stream directly and write to disk in chunks:

```csharp
// Program.cs
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the request body size limit (default is ~28 MB)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(opts =>
{
    opts.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024; // 2 GB
});

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Disable form buffering — critical for large files
    if (!request.HasFormContentType)
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected multipart/form-data");

    var boundary = request.GetMultipartBoundary();
    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(boundary))
        return Results.BadRequest("Missing boundary");

    var reader = new Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities.MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);
    var section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync();

    while (section is not null)
    {
        if (ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(section.ContentDisposition, out var cd)
            && cd.IsFileDisposition())
        {
            var fileName = Path.GetRandomFileName(); // sanitize!
            var savePath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", fileName);

            await using var fs = new FileStream(savePath, FileMode.Create);
            await section.Body.CopyToAsync(fs); // streams in 81 KB chunks
        }
        section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync();
    }

    return Results.Ok("Upload complete");
})
.DisableAntiforgery(); // if not using antiforgery tokens
```

**Key points:**

1. **`MultipartReader`** — reads the multipart body section-by-section from the network socket; never buffers the full file.
2. **`CopyToAsync`** — streams from the request body directly to the `FileStream` using an internal 81 KB buffer.
3. **Kestrel limit** — you must raise `MaxRequestBodySize`; otherwise Kestrel rejects the request before your code runs.
4. **Don't bind `[FromForm]` or `IFormFile`** — both trigger full buffering via the form model binder.

**Also add to `Program.cs` if you use form options elsewhere:**

```csharp
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(opts =>
{
    opts.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
});
```

**Required usings:**

```csharp
using Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers; // ContentDispositionHeaderValue
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Features; // FormOptions
```

This approach keeps memory usage flat (~80 KB) regardless of file size.
